Salzburg striker, Erling Braut Haaland, has flown to England for further talks with Manchester United, according to Aftenbladet. Haaland took a morning Norwegian Airlines flight from Stavanger in his homeland to Manchester Airport and was set to land at 10.15am. The 19-year-old has scored 28 goals in 22 matches for Salzburg in all competitions so far this season. Haaland is wanted by Borussia Dortmund and RB Leipzig, with the three clubs set to do battle for his signature in the January transfer window. The player has however already met United boss, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, for talks, having previously played under him at Molde. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.